   data used in this study span 3.0-5.5micrometres in wavelength and show a
   prominent CO2 absorption feature at 4.3micrometres (26-sigma
   significance). The overall spectrum is well matched by one-dimensional,
   ten-times solar metallicity models that assume
   radiative-convective-thermochemical equilibrium and have moderate cloud
   opacity. These models predict that the atmosphere should have water,
