carbon dioxide molecule (CO2), the principal component of the atmospheres of Venus
and Mars, and an important component of comets. By careful comparison and selection
of data from published laboratory investigations, we have assembled, documented,
analyzed, recommended, and make available a data file of absorption cross sections
at 25,016 wavelengths between 0.125 and 201.6 nm at room temperature.},
